The South African Weather Service forecasted a rain probability of 60 percent with a rain amount of 20mm, in Durban today. This has prompted e-Thekwini Municipality Mayor, Mxolisi Kaunda to urge motorists to exercise extreme caution while driving on wet roads as heavy rainfall is expected to continue throughout the day into the evening. The Mayor has cautioned residents living in flood-prone areas to be vigilant and alert the disaster management centre on 031 361 0000 in case of emergency. “Our disaster management teams are ready to respond and assist residents who might be affected. We also urge motorists to keep a safe following distance and to obey the rules to avoid accidents,” said Kaunda.